					<history>
						<origin notBefore="1638" notAfter="1652" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
							<p>AM 181 fol is written at <origPlace>Útskálar,
									Iceland</origPlace>. <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kålund</name> dated it to <origDate notBefore="1640" notAfter="1660">c. 1650</origDate> (<bibl>
									<ref type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">Katalog</ref>
								</bibl>), but according to Slay it was probably copied <origDate notBefore="1638" notAfter="1652">between 1638 and
									1652</origDate> (<bibl>
									<ref type="secondary-1" target="EIMF10">Slay 1972</ref>, p.
									23a</bibl>). <name type="person" key="PetSpr001">Peter
									Springborg</name>, however, thinks that the manuscript was
								mainly written in <origDate notBefore="1640" notAfter="1649">the
									1640es</origDate> (<bibl>
									<ref type="secondary-1" target="Springborg1977">Springborg
										1977</ref>
									<biblScope unit="pages">81-86</biblScope>
								</bibl>).</p>
						</origin>
						<provenance>
							<p>AM 181 fol. belonged to the man who commissioned the manuscript,
									<name type="person" key="ThoBjo003">Þorsteinn Björnsson</name>
									(<date from="1612" to="1675">1612-75</date>). Subsequently
									<foreign xml:lang="is">lögmaður</foreign>
								<name type="person" key="SigBjo001">Sigurður Björnsson</name> took
								it into possession.</p>
							<p>AM 181 a-l fol. once belonged to the same codex but they were divided
								into smaller components and AM 181 d and g-l fol. are now
								transferred to <name type="place" key="IS">Iceland</name>.</p></provenance>
					</history>
